column5: Stay up late !! starts around 130am, and an hour later the moon will be a nice red color.This event on the winter solstice happened last 370 years ago.
What were you doing on December 20 1640 hummmm !!! You woulda been what......36 years old.
Roy, you don't look a day over 270!!!
Ice fishing dude   we all know that
Our history books only had 3 paragraphs.

Take pictures, I go to sleep at 11 p.m.  I have a coin from the Vatican that's older than this event! (1634)  Back in the 90s all the planets aligned in the southwestern sky, that was a sight to see. Won't happen again until 2015 I believe.  Roy, you don't look a day over 40, I don't care what they all say. Good things come in small packages . . .
i wonder if the fishin will be better during this eclipse.It must have an effect on them.Gravitational pull and all
Have no clue Paul    I guess, only way to find out, is to go out on the water and find out
Cloudy here in Barrie, I hope it clears up.
